Practical 3

Setting up a Network File System

Step 1
Installing NFS Server :- apt-get -y install nfs-kernel-server
Step 2
Create A New Directory and file in it :- mkdir  dir_name
Step 3 
Open /etc/exports :- vi /etc/exports
Step 4 
Add Line At End Of file :- home/kali/dir_name 127.0.0.1(rw)
Step 5 
Use Below Commnand It Will Create A Table And See records :- sudo export -ra
Step 6 
Install nfs-common, if not found :- apt-get -y install nfs-common
Step 7
Mount The File And Transfer To Other Directory :- mount -t nfs 127.0.0.1:<dir_name_host> <dir_name_client>

